PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F143A1781467885
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCFinal curtain for Grampian TV
OL,4,Cas Ofcom backs STV changes
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe exact format of the 6pm programme
OL,7,Fhas still to be announced.
OL,9,FThe licence requirement is that 30pc `
OL,10,Froughly 8.5 minutes ` of the programme
OL,11,Fwill need to be different in the two
OL,12,Fregions.
OL,14,FMy understanding is that the total
OL,15,Ffigure could include sport and the
OL,16,Fweather.
OL,18,FIt will be interesting to see what
OL,19,Fformat emerges.
OL,23,EPub: 02-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,144,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14304
SC,0004
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F143A1781467885
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCFinal curtain for Grampian TV
OL,4,Cas Ofcom backs STV changes
OL,5,
OL,6,FWill the opening segments of the
OL,7,Fprogrammes be different? Or will the
OL,8,Fsplit come well into the programme?
OL,9,FPerhaps the decision will depend on the
OL,10,Fstories of the day?
OL,12,FHowever unhappy some will be with
OL,13,FOfcom, the decision has been taken. The
OL,14,Fimportant thing now is to try to make
OL,15,Fthe new format work.
OL,17,FIf STV is wise, it will try to show
OL,18,Fthat some of the criticism was
OL,19,Foverstated. It will try to ensure the
OL,20,Fshared output includes a significant
OL,21,Famount of material from the north.
OL,23,EPub: 02-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,144,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14305
SC,0005
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F143A1781467885
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCFinal curtain for Grampian TV
OL,4,Cas Ofcom backs STV changes
OL,5,
OL,6,FHowever the licence will not compel a
OL,7,Fquota.
OL,9,FIt is worth asking if Ofcom could have
OL,10,Facted differently.
OL,12,FOfcom though could argue that STV's
OL,13,Foriginal proposal would have meant no
OL,14,Fbespoke coverage of the north
OL,15,Fwhatsoever.
OL,17,FAnyone who is unhappy should ask just
OL,18,Fhow a loss-making legal requirement
OL,19,Fcould have been maintained long term.
OL,20,FSTV might simply have threatened to
OL,21,Fhand its licence back.
OL,23,EPub: 02-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,144,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14306
SC,0006
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F143A1781467885
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G6/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCFinal curtain for Grampian TV
OL,4,Cas Ofcom backs STV changes
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe big thing to consider is just how
OL,7,FPSB requirements on C3 can be
OL,8,Fmaintained.
OL,10,FIf Sky/Comcast buys ITV and, perhaps,
OL,11,FSTV then Ofcom cannot be a poodle.
OL,13,FFor now, though, the story of Grampian
OL,14,FTV is weeks from its end ` almost
OL,15,Fexactly 20 years after the name went.
OL,17,FInevitable, almost certainly. But
OL,18,Funless Ofcom or the government is
OL,19,Fprepared to move commercial TV away
OL,20,Ffrom the free market, there could be
OL,21,Fmore sad decisions ahead.
OL,23,EPub: 02-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
